abstract: “How did you say one last goodbye to Noah?”
snippet: “How did you say one last goodbye to Noah?”
lead_paragraph: A month before what would have been his son Noah’s 13th birthday, Lenny Pozner told a jury about the last time he saw him, when he dropped him off at school on Dec. 14, 2012.

abstract: Elizabeth Warren's campaign is moving to become the first in the Democratic presidential primary to hire field staff and open field offices in Pennsylvania, early moves in a late primary state that could be an important prize if the nominee remains in doubt past March.

abstract: Democrats will hold four primary debates in each of the early primary states as voting gets underway next year, with some of the debates scheduled for just days before voters head to the polls, the Democratic National Committee announced in an email to campaigns Thursday.

lead_paragraph: FRANKFURT — European Central Bank President Christine Lagarde urged the European Union on Thursday to decide which financial assets can be called "green" if it wants the ECB's help in its fight against climate change.

abstract: Amid last summer’s recession fever, we identified the key indicators to watch for signs of trouble. Five months later, the situation has improved, but risks remain.
snippet: Amid last summer’s recession fever, we identified the key indicators to watch for signs of trouble. Five months later, the situation has improved, but risks remain.
lead_paragraph: For a few weeks last summer, you would have been forgiven for thinking the United States was racing headlong into a recession. Financial markets were in turmoil, once-confident business leaders were suddenly jittery and seemingly every financial news outlet was warning that the economy was in trouble.

abstract: The Democratic National Committee announced the next set of primary debates. One will be held in each of the early-voting states.
snippet: The Democratic National Committee announced the next set of primary debates. One will be held in each of the early-voting states.
lead_paragraph: Democratic presidential candidates will debate four times in January and February as the party’s opening quartet of nominating contests approaches, the Democratic National Committee said Thursday.
